article.description: — Nicolas Elame scored 17 points as Texas-Arlington routed Mary Hardin-Baylor 104-75 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Elame leads Texas-Arlington past Mary Hardin-Baylor 104-75
article.linkText: Elame leads Texas-Arlington past Mary Hardin-Baylor 104-75
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- — Nicolas Elame scored 17 points as Texas-Arlington routed Mary Hardin-Baylor 104-75 on Saturday night. David Azore and Shemar Wilson added 15 points each for the Mavericks. Wilson also had seven rebounds. Javon Levi had 12 points and 10 assists for Texas-Arlington (1-1). It was the first time this season Texas-Arlington scored at least 100 points. Carson Hammond had 16 points for the Crusaders. Braedyn Dawes added 16 points.
